import React from 'react'
import { Dropdown } from 'semantic-ui-react'

const countryOptions = [
  { key: 'af', value: 'af', flag: 'af', text: 'Afghanistan', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ax', value: 'ax', flag: 'ax', text: 'Aland Islands', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'al', value: 'al', flag: 'al', text: 'Albania', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'dz', value: 'dz', flag: 'dz', text: 'Algeria', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'as', value: 'as', flag: 'as', text: 'American Samoa', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ad', value: 'ad', flag: 'ad', text: 'Andorra', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ao', value: 'ao', flag: 'ao', text: 'Angola', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ai', value: 'ai', flag: 'ai', text: 'Anguilla', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ag', value: 'ag', flag: 'ag', text: 'Antigua', currency: 'Af' },
  { key: 'ar', value: 'ar', flag: 'ar', text: 'Argentina', currency: 'Af' },

]

const DropdownExampleSearchSelection = () => (
  <Dropdown
    placeholder='Select Country'
    fluid
    search
    selection
    options={countryOptions}
  />
)

export default DropdownExampleSearchSelection
